column5: This guy hit a crankbait in a shollow bay on a deep water north type lake. it resembles a chub but was 12" long. purple hue to the scales and soft finned.
Too dark for a Fallfish, it's a Springer.  Hamilton looks like they are loosing another 38-22 BC, 4th quarter, man.
Shefish/ fallfish... have caught lots of them in Algonquin
We always called them white fish as kids?
We called them whitefish too but it's actually a fall fish. Did it make gulping noises?  They actually fight pretty hard for their size.
forget what its called...how did it taste? Looks like great musky bait.
We catch them in the Ottawa river and use them as pike bait under a float. None better
i didnt notice it making any noises, released it right after photo. looked like nice pike bait
